The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi, Aug. 13: Bahujan Samaj Party and BJP councillors came to blows today at a Municipal Corporation of Delhi session and tore one anothers clothes.

 BSP councillors, upset with mayor Arti Mehra for not being allowed to speak, rushed to the well. Councillors of the ruling BJP immediately got on their feet. This set off a free-for-all with many councillors suffering minor injuries. The BJP members, who outnumbered the BSP councillors, pushed their opponents out of the House.

 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has cancelled the anticipatory bail of Gujarat DSP Narender K. Amin, who was allegedly involved in the Sohrabbudin Sheikh fake encounter case. However, it refused to give any directive to Andhra Pradesh police for allegedly helping out their Gujarat counterparts in killing Sohrabbudin and three others.

 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court on Monday took serious note of the CBI and the Centres tardy probe into the Kargil-related defence deals that allegedly cost the exchequer Rs 2,000 crore. The court asked the defence ministry to file a status report on action taken against errant officers.

 Kanpur (PTI): A girl died after she fell while playing musical chairs on Monday, police said. Naina Samtani, a BSc first-year student, suffered serious head injuries when she fell after someone pulled the chair away from her.

 Kuala Lumpur (PTI): An Indian jeweller has been robbed of jewellery worth Rs 1 crore that he had brought for an exhibition. A security guard at a five-star hotel informed Sanjay Kumar that his room had been broken into while he was out.

 Mumbai (PTI): Twenty kilograms of ammonium nitrate, used to make explosives, have been seized by octroi agents from an unidentified man at Aurangabad station. The man dropped the bag containing the explosives and fled.




